{"title_page": "Bachelor of Computer Application", "text_new": "'''Bachelor of Computer Applications''' ('''BCA''') is a four-year [[undergraduate degree]] in [[education in Nepal|Nepal]] and three-year undergraduate degree course in [[education in India|India]]. With a BCA, students can study for a [[master's degree|masters]] in [[Master in Computer Application|computer application]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://beta.nielit.gov.in/kohima/content/syllabus-bachelor-computer-application-bca|title=Syllabus for Bachelor of Computer Application|website=National Institute of Electronics & Information Technology, Kohima}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msuniv.ac.in/|title=Manonmaniam Sundaranar University|last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suniv.ac.in/ |title=Sambalpur University |last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ggu.ac.in |title=Guru Ghasidas University |last=|first=|date=|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe BCA is a common degree for [[computer science|CS]]/[[information technology|IT]] students at [[List of universities in India|Indian universities]], and is an alternative to the [[engineering]] counterpart, the B.E/B.Tech in [[Computer Science and Engineering]]/IT, which requires 4 years of study. It is a technical degree that prepares students for a career in the field of computer applications and [[software development]], this being a professional course, even non-math students can also opt for this course, many universities offer this course in India.\nThis is a good course for non-math student so they also can make their career in [[Information technology]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://targetstudy.com/courses/bca.html |title=B.C.A., Bachelor of Computer Applications, Syllabus, Eligibility, Duration, Degree Course |publisher=Targetstudy.com |date=2018-03-27 |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cbsmohali.org/bca.html |title=Bachelors in Computer Applications (BCA) |publisher=Cbsmohali.org |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uni-mysore.ac.in/ |title=UNIVERSITY OF MYSORE &#124; \u0cae\u0cc8\u0cb8\u0cc2\u0cb0\u0cc1 \u0cb5\u0cbf\u0cb6\u0ccd\u0cb5\u0cb5\u0cbf\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0caf\u0cbe\u0ca8\u0cbf\u0cb2\u0caf |publisher=Uni-mysore.ac.in |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.universityofcalicut.info/ |title=Official website of Calicut University - Home |publisher=Universityofcalicut.info |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://uem.edu.in/uem-jaipur/ |title=University of Engineering & Management(UEM), Jaipur |publisher=uem.edu.in/uem-jaipur/ |date= |accessdate=2019-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unom.ac.in/ |title=Welcome to University of Madras |publisher=Unom.ac.in |date= |accessdate=2018-04-22}}</ref>\n\nThe study period of BCA includes various subjects such as Programming in C Language (Basic and Advanced), Networking, World-Wide-Web, Data Structure, Advanced C Language Programming, Database Management, Mathematics, Software Engineering, Object Oriented Programming using C++, Visual Basic, Programming using PHP, JAVA, Oracle, Operating Systems, Web Scripting and Development, etc.\n\n<h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>\nStudents all streams (science, commerce & arts) can pursue BCA. According to general eligibility criteria, a candidate needs to score at-least  45% - 60% or even just passing marks in +2 to be eligible for admission into BCA course. The eligibility criteria for BCA is different for every college and university. Some colleges may provide direct admission whereas others may provide admission only on the basis of merit lists, entrance exams or even personal/group interviews. Not every university will provide admission to arts/humanities stream students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogsbyvibhor.blogspot.com/2019/09/bca.html|title=Everything you need to know about BCA|website=Blogs By Vibhor}}</ref>\n\n<h2>Syllabus</h2>\nThe general syllabus is shared as it is updated every year.\n\n<h4>Semester 1</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>Computer Fundamental and Office Automation</li>\n<li>Programming Principles and Algorithm</li>\n<li>Principle of Management</li>\n<li>Business Communication</li>\n<li>Mathematics - 1</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Semester 2</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>C - Programming</li>\n<li>Digital Electronics and Computer Organization</li>\n<li>Organization Behavior</li>\n<li>Financial Accounting and Management</li>\n<li>Mathematics - 2</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Semester 3</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>Object Oriented Programming using C++</li>\n<li>Data Structures using C</li>\n<li>Business Economics</li>\n<li>Computer Architecture and Assembly Language</li>\n<li>Elements of Statistics</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Semester 4</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>Computer Graphics</li>\n<li>Operating System</li>\n<li>Software Engineering</li>\n<li>Optimization Techniques</li>\n<li>Mathematics - 3</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Semester 5</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>Introduction to DBMS</li>\n<li>Java Programming</li>\n<li>Computer Network</li>\n<li>Numerical Method</li>\n<li>Minor Project</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Semester 6</h4>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle;\">\n<li>Computer Network Security</li>\n<li>E-Commerce</li>\n<li>Knowledge Management</li>\n<li>Information Systems</li>\n<li>Major Project</li>\n</ul>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Academic degrees of India]]\n[[Category:Bachelor's degrees|Computer Applications, Bachelor of]]\n[[Category:Computer science education]]\n[[Category:Computers and the environment]]\n", "text_old": "'''Bachelor of Computer Applications''' ('''BCA''') is a four-year [[undergraduate degree]] in [[education in Nepal|Nepal]] and three-year undergraduate degree course in [[education in India|India]]. With a BCA, students can study for a [[master's degree|masters]] in [[Master in Computer Application|compute