{"title_page": "Raymond Van Gestel", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Raymond Van Gestel\n|image          = Raymond_Van_Gestel.jpg\n|image_size     = 240px\n|caption        = Raymond Van Gestel in 1953\n|fullname       = \n|birth_date     = {{birth date|1930|1|20|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Mol, Belgium|Mol]], Belgium\n|death_date     = {{death date and age|2020|4|17|1930|1|20|df=y}}\n|death_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = [[Midfielder#Winger|Right winger]]\n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = \n|years1         = 1946\u20131948\n|clubs1         = [[SV Mol]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 1948\u20131958\n|clubs2         = [[K. Lyra]]\n|caps2          = 168\n|goals2         = 92\n|years3         = 1958\u20131962\n|clubs3         = [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]]\n|caps3          = \n|goals3         = \n|totalcaps      = 168+\n|totalgoals     = 92+\n|nationalyears1 = 1951\u20131953\n|nationalteam1  = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 5\n|nationalgoals1 = 2\n}}\n'''Raymond (Mon) Van Gestel''' ([[Arendonk]], 20 January [[1930]] - [[Mol,_Belgium|Mol]], 17 april [[2020]]) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[Football player]] and [[Aircraft_pilot|pilot]].<ref name=\"lyralierse\">[https://lyralierse.be/nieuws/mon-van-gestel-overleden/ Mon Van Gestel overleden] lyralierse.be, 19 april 2020, source in Dutch</ref> Most of his career he played for [[K._Lyra|Lyra]] in [[Lier,_Belgium|Lier]].<ref name=\"hln3\">[https://www.hln.be/sport/voetbal/rode-duivels/voormalig-rode-duivel-en-luchtvaarticoon-mon-van-gestel-sterft-op-90-jarige-leeftijd~a32dc6b2/ Voormalig Rode Duivel en luchtvaarticoon Mon Van Gestel sterft op 90-jarige leeftijd] hln.be, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Mol, Belgium|Mol]], Van Gestel played for [[SV Mol]], [[K. Lyra]] and [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=25872|accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\nIn total he played 57 games in the [[Belgian_First_Division_A|first division]] scoring a total of 32 goals.<ref>[http://users.skynet.be/fb304341/ Belgiumsoccerhistory (Peter Mari\u00ebn), website in Dutch]</ref>\nIn 1954, when Lyra promoted to the first divion, he suffered a severe injury at the knee and his professionel (international) career was large finished.<ref name=\"hoeishetmet\"/> In total he achieved 168 official games for [[K. Lyra]] in which he made 92 goals.<ref>[https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/25872/Raymond_Van_Gestel.html Van Gestel, Raymond national-football-teams.com, statistics]</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Broes |first1=Hugo |last2=Mari\u00ebn |first2=Peter |title=Kon. Lyra TSV 100 Plus {{!}} De Slegte |date=2016 |pages=294 |edition=1 |url=https://www.deslegte.be/kon-lyra-tsv-100-plus-1616378/ |language=nl-BE}}</ref>\nDuring his career he earned earned 5 caps for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian national team]] between 1951 and 1953<ref name = \"NFT\"/> scoring 2 goals. Both goals were against Spain on the 10 of June 1951. The first goal he scored was after only 17 seconds in the game, giving him the record of the fastest goal scored for the [[Belgium_national_football_team|national team]].<ref>[https://lyralierse.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/LYRALIERSE_magazine_NR1.pdf Nog meer straffe internationals] lyralierse.be, K. Lyra-Lierse Clubmagazine, blz. 21, article in Dutch</ref><ref name=\"lyralierse\"/> His superb game against Spain gave him the nickname ''Raimundo el rapido'' and he almost got a transfer to Espanyol, but Lyra refused a transfer.<ref>[https://sporza.be/nl/2020/04/19/rode-duivel-die-na-17-seconden-tegen-spanje-scoort-is-niet-meer~1587331282847/ Rode Duivel die na 17 seconden tegen Spanje scoort, is niet meer] sporza.be, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref> \nCurrently, the record is 8,1 seconds, set by [[Christian_Benteke|Benteke]] against [[Gibraltar_national_football_team|Gibraltar]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37602916 Belgium's Christian Benteke scored the fastest ever World Cup qualifying goal after 8.1 seconds against Gibraltar] bbc.com, 10 October 2016</ref>\nIn 1954 he was selected for the [[1954_FIFA_World_Cup|World Cup]] in Z\u00fcrich, but he could not join the team due to a military mission in Africa as a fighterpilot for the [[Belgian_Air_Component|Belgian air force]].<ref name=\"hoeishetmet\">[https://www.rtv.be/artikels/hoe-het-met-mon-van-gestel-a55976 Hie is het met? Mon Van Gestel] rtv.be, 24 juni 2018, article in Dutch</ref>\n\nNext to being a football player he was also active as an athlete in [[Track_and_field|the long jump and sprints]]. He was, e.g., the belgian champion in the [[long jump]].<ref name=\"onderox\">[http://www.onderox.be/nieuws/539/mon-van-gestel-held-op-het-sportveld-en-in-het-luchtruim Mon Van Gestel: held op het sportveld en in het luchtruim] onderox.be, Jef Aerts, article in Dutch</ref> Due to his versatility he is one of the few (or only one) Belgian athletes ever to compete in different sports at an international level in the same year(s).<ref name=\"hln2\"/>\n\n==Later life and death==\nAside from being an athlete Raymond was a [[Fighter pilot]] for the Belgian airforce and flight instructor.<ref name=\"motorvliegen\">[https://www.motorvliegen.be/files/fly-in-magazine-2018.pdf Keiheuvel fly-in 2018] motorvliegen.be, 2018, blz. 6</ref><ref>[https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/ggv109kic Vlieginstructeur analyseert dodelijke crash] nieuwsblad.be, 16 augustus 2006</ref> As an instructor he trained around 2000 students.<ref>[https://www.rtv.be/artikels/luchtvaarticoon-en-ex-rode-duivel-mon-van-gestel-90-overleden-a81641 Luchtvaarticoon en ex-Rode Duivel Mon Van Gestel (90) overleden] rtv.be, 18 april 2020</ref> Together with his brother he was also one of the founding members of the Belgian [[Flying club]] Keiheuvel<ref name=\"hln2\">[https://www.hln.be/in-de-buurt/balen/gewezen-rode-duivel-en-mede-oprichter-van-vliegclub-keiheuvel-mon-van-gestel-90-overleden-zijn-veelzijdigheid-was-indrukwekkend~adc7b8f5/ Gewezen Rode Duivel en mede-oprichter van vliegclub Keiheuvel Mon Van Gestel (90) overleden: \u201cZijn veelzijdigheid was indrukwekkend] hln.be, Wouter Demuynck, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref><ref name=\"gva\">[https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20200419_04927290/ex-rode-duivel-en-bezieler-aeroclub-keiheuvel-overleden Ex-Rode Duivel en bezieler Aeroclub Keiheuvel overleden] gva.be, mto, 19 april 2020, article in dutch</ref>\nHe died on 17 April 2020, aged 90.<ref name=\"gva\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Gestel, Raymond}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Belgian footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgium international footballers]]\n[[Category:K. Lyra players]]\n[[Category:K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Belgian Second Division/Belgian First Division B players]]\n\n{{Belgium-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belgian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Raymond Van Gestel\n|image          = Raymond_Van_Gestel.jpg\n|image_size     = 240px\n|caption        = Raymond Van Gestel in 1953\n|fullname       = \n|birth_date     = {{birth date|1930|1|20|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Mol, Belgium|Mol]], Belgium\n|death_date     = {{death date and age|2020|4|17|1930|1|20|df=y}}\n|death_place    = \n|height         = \n|position       = [[Midfielder#Winger|Right winger]]\n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = \n|years1         = 1946\u20131948\n|clubs1         = [[SV Mol]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 1948\u20131958\n|clubs2         = [[K. Lyra]]\n|caps2          = 168\n|goals2         = 92\n|years3         = 1958\u20131962\n|clubs3         = [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]]\n|caps3          = \n|goals3         = \n|totalcaps      = 168+\n|totalgoals     = 92+\n|nationalyears1 = 1951\u20131953\n|nationalteam1  = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 5\n|nationalgoals1 = 2\n}}\n'''Raymond (Mon) Van Gestel''' ([[Arendonk]], 20 January [[1930]] - [[Mol,_Belgium|Mol]], 17 april [[2020]]) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[Football player]] and [[Aircraft_pilot|pilot]].<ref name=\"lyralierse\">[https://lyralierse.be/nieuws/mon-van-gestel-overleden/ Mon Van Gestel overleden] lyralierse.be, 19 april 2020, source in Dutch</ref> Most of his career he played for [[K._Lyra|Lyra]] in [[Lier,_Belgium|Lier]].<ref name=\"hln3\">[https://www.hln.be/sport/voetbal/rode-duivels/voormalig-rode-duivel-en-luchtvaarticoon-mon-van-gestel-sterft-op-90-jarige-leeftijd~a32dc6b2/ Voormalig Rode Duivel en luchtvaarticoon Mon Van Gestel sterft op 90-jarige leeftijd] hln.be, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Mol, Belgium|Mol]], Van Gestel played for [[SV Mol]], [[K. Lyra]] and [[K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel|Verbroedering Geel]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=25872|accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\nIn total he played 57 games in the [[Belgian_First_Division_A|first division]] scoring a total of 32 goals.<ref>[http://users.skynet.be/fb304341/ Belgiumsoccerhistory (Peter Mari\u00ebn), website in Dutch]</ref>\nIn 1954, when Lyra promoted to the first divion, he suffered a severe injury at the knee and his professionel (international) career was large finished.<ref name=\"hoeishetmet\"/> In total he achieved 168 official games for [[K. Lyra]] in which he made 92 goals.<ref>[https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/25872/Raymond_Van_Gestel.html Van Gestel, Raymond national-football-teams.com, statistics]</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Broes |first1=Hugo |last2=Mari\u00ebn |first2=Peter |title=Kon. Lyra TSV 100 Plus {{!}} De Slegte |date=2016 |pages=294 |edition=1 |url=https://www.deslegte.be/kon-lyra-tsv-100-plus-1616378/ |language=nl-BE}}</ref>\nDuring his career he earned earned 5 caps for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian national team]] between 1951 and 1953<ref name = \"NFT\"/> scoring 2 goals. Both goals were against Spain on the 10 of June 1951. The first goal he scored was after only 17 seconds in the game, giving him the record of the fastest goal scored ever for the [[Belgium_national_football_team|national team]].<ref>[https://lyralierse.be/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/LYRALIERSE_magazine_NR1.pdf Nog meer straffe internationals] lyralierse.be, K. Lyra-Lierse Clubmagazine, blz. 21, article in Dutch</ref><ref name=\"lyralierse\"/> His superb game against Spain gave him the nickname ''Raimundo el rapido'' and he almost got a transfer to Espanyol, but Lyra refused a transfer.<ref>[https://sporza.be/nl/2020/04/19/rode-duivel-die-na-17-seconden-tegen-spanje-scoort-is-niet-meer~1587331282847/ Rode Duivel die na 17 seconden tegen Spanje scoort, is niet meer] sporza.be, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref> \nCurrently, the record is 8,1 seconds, set by [[Christian_Benteke|Benteke]] against [[Gibraltar_national_football_team|Gibraltar]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37602916 Belgium's Christian Benteke scored the fastest ever World Cup qualifying goal after 8.1 seconds against Gibraltar] bbc.com, 10 October 2016</ref>\nIn 1954 he was selected for the [[1954_FIFA_World_Cup|World Cup]] in Z\u00fcrich, but he could not join the team due to a military mission in Africa as a fighterpilot for the [[Belgian_Air_Component|Belgian air force]].<ref name=\"hoeishetmet\">[https://www.rtv.be/artikels/hoe-het-met-mon-van-gestel-a55976 Hie is het met? Mon Van Gestel] rtv.be, 24 juni 2018, article in Dutch</ref>\n\nNext to being a football player he was also active as an athlete in [[Track_and_field|the long jump and sprints]]. He was, e.g., the belgian champion in the [[long jump]].<ref name=\"onderox\">[http://www.onderox.be/nieuws/539/mon-van-gestel-held-op-het-sportveld-en-in-het-luchtruim Mon Van Gestel: held op het sportveld en in het luchtruim] onderox.be, Jef Aerts, article in Dutch</ref> Due to his versatility he is one of the few (or only one) Belgian athletes ever to compete in different sports at an international level in the same year(s).<ref name=\"hln2\"/>\n\n==Later life and death==\nAside from being an athlete Raymond was a [[Fighter pilot]] for the Belgian airforce and flight instructor.<ref name=\"motorvliegen\">[https://www.motorvliegen.be/files/fly-in-magazine-2018.pdf Keiheuvel fly-in 2018] motorvliegen.be, 2018, blz. 6</ref><ref>[https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/ggv109kic Vlieginstructeur analyseert dodelijke crash] nieuwsblad.be, 16 augustus 2006</ref> As an instructor he trained around 2000 students.<ref>[https://www.rtv.be/artikels/luchtvaarticoon-en-ex-rode-duivel-mon-van-gestel-90-overleden-a81641 Luchtvaarticoon en ex-Rode Duivel Mon Van Gestel (90) overleden] rtv.be, 18 april 2020</ref> Together with his brother he was also one of the founding members of the Belgian [[Flying club]] Keiheuvel<ref name=\"hln2\">[https://www.hln.be/in-de-buurt/balen/gewezen-rode-duivel-en-mede-oprichter-van-vliegclub-keiheuvel-mon-van-gestel-90-overleden-zijn-veelzijdigheid-was-indrukwekkend~adc7b8f5/ Gewezen Rode Duivel en mede-oprichter van vliegclub Keiheuvel Mon Van Gestel (90) overleden: \u201cZijn veelzijdigheid was indrukwekkend] hln.be, Wouter Demuynck, 19 april 2020, article in Dutch</ref><ref name=\"gva\">[https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20200419_04927290/ex-rode-duivel-en-bezieler-aeroclub-keiheuvel-overleden Ex-Rode Duivel en bezieler Aeroclub Keiheuvel overleden] gva.be, mto, 19 april 2020, article in dutch</ref>\nHe died on 17 April 2020, aged 90.<ref name=\"gva\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Van Gestel, Raymond}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Belgian footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgium international footballers]]\n[[Category:K. Lyra players]]\n[[Category:K.F.C. Verbroedering Geel players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Belgian Second Division/Belgian First Division B players]]\n\n{{Belgium-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Garnhami", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_Van_Gestel"}
{"title_page": "Morgan Wallen", "text_new": "{{short description|American country music singer and songwriter}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Morgan Wallen\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Morgan Cole Wallen\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1993|05|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Sneedville, Tennessee]]\n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Country music|Country]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar\n}}\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = [[Big Loud Records|Big Loud]]\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|morganwallen.com}}\n}}\n'''Morgan Cole Wallen''' (born May 13, 1993) is an American [[country music]] singer and songwriter. He is signed to [[Big Loud Records]] and has released four singles: \"The Way I Talk\", \"[[Up Down (Morgan Wallen song)|Up Down]]\", which features [[Florida Georgia Line]], \"[[Whiskey Glasses]]\", and his current single \"[[Chasin' You]]\".\n\n==Early life==\nWallen was born in [[Sneedville, Tennessee]].<ref name=\"nash\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2017/03/13/whos-new-morgan-wallen-2/|title=Who\u2019s New: Morgan Wallen|last=Casey|first=Jim|date=March 13, 2017|work=Nash Country Daily|accessdate=April 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085547/http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2017/03/13/whos-new-morgan-wallen-2/|archive-date=April 24, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> His father was a Baptist pastor and as a child, Wallen took piano and violin lessons. He was offered a scholarship to play baseball in college, but after an injury, chose to pursue music instead.\n\n==Career==\n===2014: ''The Voice''===\nIn 2014, Wallen competed on [[The Voice (U.S. season 6)|season 6]] of ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'', initially as part of [[Usher (musician)|Usher]]'s team and later [[Adam Levine]]'s team. He was eliminated during the Playoffs.<ref name=\"nash\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Stage\n! scope=\"col\" | Song\n! scope=\"col\" | Original artist\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Order\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Blind Audition\n| \"[[Collide (Howie Day song)|Collide]]\"\n| [[Howie Day]]\n| March 4, 2014\n| 4.2\n| [[Shakira]] and [[Usher (musician)|Usher]] turned<br />Joined Team Usher\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Battles, Round 1\n| \"[[Hey Brother]]\" <small>(vs. Brothers Walker)</small>\n| [[Avicii]]\n| March 18, 2014\n| 9.5\n| Saved by Coach\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Battles, Round 2\n| \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]]\" <small>(vs. Stevie Jo)</small>\n| [[One Direction]]\n| April 1, 2014\n| 15.4\n| Defeated<br>Stolen by [[Adam Levine]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Playoffs\n| \"[[Stay (Black Stone Cherry song)|Stay]]\"\n| [[Florida Georgia Line]]\n| April 14, 2014\n| 18.9\n| Eliminated\n|}\n\n===2016\u2013present: Big Loud Records and ''If I Know Me''===\nIn late 2016, Wallen signed to [[Big Loud Records]], a label owned by record producer [[Joey Moi]]. He released his debut single \"The Way I Talk\" soon afterward.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicrow.com/2016/09/big-loud-records-morgan-wallen-trades-baseball-ambitions-for-country-music-dreams/|title=Big Loud Records\u2019 Morgan Wallen Trades Baseball Ambitions For Country Music Dreams|last=Nicholson|first=Jessica|date=September 27, 2016|work=[[MusicRow]]|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> In addition, he co-wrote the [[A Thousand Horses]] single \"Preachin' to the Choir\".<ref name=\"nash\"/> In April 2017, Wallen released a [[music video]] for \"The Way I Talk\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundslikenashville.com/news/morgan-wallen-celebrates-upbringing-video-way-talk/|title=Morgan Wallen Celebrates Upbringing in Video for \u2018The Way I Talk\u2019|last=Brickey|first=Kelly|date=April 9, 2017|work=Sounds Like Nashville|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> He also joined [[Florida Georgia Line]] for set dates on their [[Dig Your Roots Tour]].<ref name=\"nash\"/>\n\nOn April 27, 2018, Wallen released his debut album, ''[[If I Know Me (album)|If I Know Me]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.radio.com/blogs/lauren-hoffman/exclusive-morgan-wallens-debut-album-if-i-know-me-reveals-what-hes-all-about |title=EXCLUSIVE: Morgan Wallen's Debut Album 'If I Know Me' Reveals What He's All About|date=April 26, 2018|first=Lauren |last= Hoffman |work=Radio.com }}</ref><ref>Jon Freeman, (June 19, 2018) [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/how-up-down-singer-morgan-wallen-turned-his-accent-into-an-honest-country-voice-666096/ ''Rolling Stone'']</ref> The second single from the album, \"[[Up Down (Morgan Wallen song)|Up Down]]\", was recorded with Florida Georgia Line.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8289658/morgan-wallen-up-down-hot-100-interview |title=How 'Up Down' Singer Morgan Wallen Went From Singing at Bonfires to Collaborating With Florida Georgia Line |date=April 19, 2018 |first= Tatiana |last=Cirisano }}</ref> According to Wallen, he and Florida Georgia Line got together as they knew each other, and when FGL heard the single, they became interested in a collaboration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.megacountry.com/videos/14321-morgan-wallen-talks-fgl-collab |title=Morgan Wallen Talks New Single Collab with Florida Georgia Line |work=MegaCountry }}</ref> The album's third single \"[[Whiskey Glasses]]\" released to country radio on July 30, 2018. It reached at number one on the [[Country Airplay]] in June 2019. Wallen joined Florida Georgia Line on their [[Can't Say I Ain't Country Tour]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onecountry.com/country-artists/florida-georgia-line-announce-tour-dates/|title=Florida Georgia Line Announce Can\u2019t Say I Ain\u2019t Country Tour with Dan + Shay|last=Konicki|first=Lisa|date=2019-01-09|website=One Country|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref> Wallen also made a short appearance on the December 3, 2018 episode of ''[[WWE Raw]]''. \"Whiskey Glasses\" went on to become the year-end number one song on country radio for 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bulletins.billboard.com/country/country_update_1209.pdf|title=Billboard Country Update|date=December 9, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Wallen released \"[[Chasin' You]]\" to country radio as the fourth single from ''If I Know Me'' in July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2019/07/09/morgan-wallen-to-release-smoldering-new-single-chasin-you-listen/|title=Morgan Wallen to Release Smoldering New Single, \"Chasin\u2019 You\" [Listen]|last=Casey|first=Jim|website=Nash Country Daily|publisher=Cumulus Media|date=July 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tasteofcountry.com/morgan-wallen-chasin-you-single/|title=Morgan Wallen Is Still After an Ex in New Single \u2018Chasin\u2019 You\u2019 [Listen]|website=Taste of Country|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/TLP |title=Morgan Wallen Chart History: Billboard 200 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Albums\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CLP |title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Top Country Albums) |work=Billboard |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2019/3/aria-chart-watch-517/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #517|publisher=auspOp|date=March 23, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2019}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CNA |title=Morgan Wallen Chart History: Canadian Albums |work=Billboard |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[If I Know Me (album)|If I Know Me]]''\n|\n* Release date: April 27, 2018\n* Label: [[Big Loud Records|Big Loud]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 23 || 3 || 53 || 45\n|\n*US: 50,700<ref>{{cite web |url=http://roughstock.com/news/2020/03/44165-top-10-country-albums-pure-sales-chart-march-9-2020|title=Top 10 Country Albums Pure Sales Chart: March 9, 2020 |work=RoughStock|first=Matt |last=Bjorke |date= March 10, 2020 |accessdate=March 22, 2020 }}</ref>\n|\n* [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Gold{{Certification Cite Ref|region=United States |artist=Morgan Wallen |refname=\"RIAA\"}}\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:17em;\"| Details\n!| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Sales\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Albums\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''The Way I Talk''\n|\n* Release date: July 29, 2016\n* Label: Big Loud Mountain\n* Format: Digital download\n| \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Morgan Wallen''\n|\n* Release date: January 12, 2018\n* Label: Big Loud Mountain\n* Format: Digital download\n| 45\n|\n* US: 1,300<ref>{{cite news |url=http://roughstock.com/news/2018/04/42954-top-10-country-album-sales-chart-april-9-2018 |title=Top 10 Country Album Sales Chart: April 9, 2018 |first=Matt |last=Bjorke |date=April 9, 2018 |work=Roughstock |accessdate=April 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"font-size:8pt\"| \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"5\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Certifications\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br /><ref name=\"Billboard Hot 100\">{{cite web|title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Hot 100) |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/HSI |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Hot Country Songs|US Country]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Songs\">{{cite web|title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Hot Country Songs) |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CSI |website=Billboard |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Country Airplay|US Country Airplay]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Airplay\">{{cite web|title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Country Airplay) |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CSA |website=Billboard |accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canada Country|CAN Country]]<br /><ref name=\"Canada Country\">{{cite web|title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Canada Country) |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CCW |website=Billboard |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"Canada Hot 100\">{{cite web|title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Canadian Hot 100) |url=https://www.billboard.com/music