ng and after his career. In August 1997, he pleaded [[Nolo contendere|no contest]] to four [[misdemeanor]] charges of abusing a former girlfriend and was sentenced to one year in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/19/sports/robertson-sentenced-to-jail.html |title=Robertson Sentenced to Jail |date=August 19, 1997 |work=New York Times |accessdate=April 20, 2007}}</ref> He also spent a month in jail during the 1990 NBA off-season on domestic assault charges against his then-wife. Robertson was arrested again in [[San Antonio, Texas|San Antonio]] in January 2007, on a variety of charges, several related to [[domestic violence]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nba/news/story?id=2751379 |title=Former Spurs star Robertson arrested on six warrants |date=February 1, 2007 |publisher=ESPN.com |accessdate=April 20, 2007}}</ref>\n\nOn February 26, 2010, Robertson was arrested for the alleged sexual assault of a child, trafficking an underage child for purposes of sex and forcing a sexual performance by a child. Authorities claim that Robertson was part of a ring that kidnapped a 14-year-old girl from San Antonio, forced her to have sex with clients and to dance at a [[Corpus Christi, Texas|Corpus Christi]] strip club in 2009. The girl escaped her alleged captors, prompting an investigation. It was determined that the entire story was made up. There is still no explanation on why the accuser made this story up.'''<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nbcsports.msnbc.com/id/35606969/ns/sports-nba/ |title=Ex-NBA All-Star accused of sex trafficking |date=February 26, 2010 |publisher=msnbc.com |accessdate=February 26, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100228141646/http://nbcsports.msnbc.com/id/35606969/ns/sports-nba/ |archivedate=February 28, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Gonzales |first1=Eileen |title=Ex-Spur Arrested In Human Trafficking Probe |url=http://www.ksat.com/news/22682025/detail.html |website=ksat.com |accessdate=July 3, 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611041410/http://www.ksat.com/news/22682025/detail.html |archivedate=June 11, 2011 |date=February 26, 2010}}</ref>''' Robertson was found not guilty of all charges on November 30, 2015.'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Charges against Alvin Robertson related to alleged sex ring dismissed |url=http://www.espn.com/nba/story/_/id/14264061/sex-trafficking-charges-ex-san-antonio-spur-alvin-robertson-dismissed |website=ESPN.com |accessdate=July 3, 2018 |date=December 1, 2015}}</ref>'''\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports}}\n* [[List of National Basketball Association career steals leaders]]\n* [[List of National Basketball Association players with most steals in a game]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{basketballstats|bbr=r/roberal01}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Footer 1984 Olympic Champions Basketball Men}}\n{{1984 NBA Draft}}\n{{NBA Defensive Players of the Year}}\n{{NBA Most Improved Players}}\n{{NBA steals leaders}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robertson, Alvin}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American basketball players]]\n[[Category:All-American college men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American expatriate basketball people in Canada]]\n[[Category:American men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of assault]]\n[[Category:Arkansas Razorbacks men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Ohio]]\n[[Category:Crowder College alumni]]\n[[Category:Detroit Pistons players]]\n[[Category:Florida Beachdogs players]]\n[[Category:Junior college men's basketball players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Milwaukee Bucks players]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association All-Stars]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for the United States in basketball]]\n[[Category:People from Barberton, Ohio]]\n[[Categ